---
import SiteShell from '../../layouts/SiteShell.astro';

const title = 'Services | ZeroBeatLabs';
const description =
  'Choose between governed agentic workflow automation for live systems and a fixed-scope IT reporting workflow sprint using sanitized exports.';

const pageSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'CollectionPage',
  name: 'ZeroBeatLabs Services',
  url: 'https://zerobeatlabs.org/services/',
  description,
  mainEntity: {
    '@type': 'ItemList',
    itemListElement: [
      {
        '@type': 'ListItem',
        position: 1,
        url: 'https://zerobeatlabs.org/services/agentic-workflows/',
        name: 'Governed Agentic Workflows',
      },
      {
        '@type': 'ListItem',
        position: 2,
        url: 'https://zerobeatlabs.org/services/it-reporting/',
        name: 'IT Reporting Workflow Sprint',
      },
    ],
  },
};
---

<SiteShell title={title} description={description} activePage="services" structuredData={pageSchema}>
  <section class="hero" aria-labelledby="services-hero">
    <div class="wrap hero-grid">
      <div class="hero-copy">
        <nav class="breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <a href="/#home">Home</a><span aria-hidden="true">/</span><span>Services</span>
        </nav>
        <p class="eyebrow">Services</p>
        <h1 id="services-hero">Choose the level of access the work actually needs.</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          Begin with sanitized exports and a fixed reporting outcome, or map a
          live-system workflow with scoped access, explicit authority, and human ownership.
        </p>
      </div>
      <aside class="hero-side" aria-label="Service principle">
        <p class="label">One rule across both services</p>
        <p>Define the inputs, authority, validation, owner, and recovery path before the work moves.</p>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-soft" aria-labelledby="service-options">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <p class="eyebrow">Service ladder</p>
        <h2 id="service-options">Two controlled ways to start.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="service-grid">
        <article class="service-card">
          <p class="label">Live systems · human-governed</p>
          <h3>Governed Agentic Workflows</h3>
          <p>
            A paid Workflow and Governance Blueprint followed by a controlled pilot
            or custom fixed-scope implementation. Live work uses client-owned,
            revocable, least-privilege access.
          </p>
          <ul class="plain-list">
            <li>Workflow map and acceptance standard</li>
            <li>Permission and approval matrix</li>
            <li>Exceptions, kill switch, and manual fallback</li>
            <li>Handoff plus optional bounded support</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="card-actions">
            <a class="button" href="/services/agentic-workflows/">Explore Agentic Workflows</a>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="service-card reporting-card">
          <p class="label">Sanitized exports · no credentials</p>
          <h3>IT Reporting Workflow Sprint</h3>
          <p class="price">$1,250 introductory fixed price for the first two engagements</p>
          <p>
            Up to two sanitized export types become one completed weekly or monthly
            report, a reusable template, QA controls, and a written runbook.
          </p>
          <div class="card-actions">
            <a class="button" href="/services/it-reporting/">See the Reporting Sprint</a>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="service-method">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">How we work</p>
      <h2 id="service-method">Map → Bound → Pilot → Prove and hand off.</h2>
      <p class="lede">
        The amount of access changes by service. The operating discipline does not:
        validation, human ownership, documented limits, and a recoverable path stay visible.
      </p>
      <p><a class="button button-secondary" href="/#process">See the full method</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-ink" aria-labelledby="services-contact">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">Not sure which fits?</p>
      <h2 id="services-contact">Start with the workflow and its consequences.</h2>
      <p class="lede">
        A short workflow mapping call is enough to decide whether the work belongs in the
        no-credential Reporting Sprint or needs a governed live-system Blueprint.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="button" href="https://calendar.app.google/ZzgzTAhCFCk1oxBH8">Book a 10-minute workflow mapping call</a>
        <a class="button button-secondary" href="/#contact">See contact options</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</SiteShell>
